---
import ServiceLayout from '../../layouts/ServiceLayout.astro';

const description = 'Native iOS and macOS app development with Swift, SwiftUI, and AppKit, from focused prototype to App Store release.';
---

<ServiceLayout
  title="iOS & macOS development"
  description={description}
  serviceType="Native iOS and macOS application development"
  slug="ios-macos-development"
>
  <h2>Native where native matters</h2>
  <p>I build focused Apple-platform apps with Swift, SwiftUI, and AppKit. Native development is a good fit when the product depends on platform conventions, offline work, privacy, keyboard support, or the details that make a Mac or iPhone app feel like it belongs there.</p>

  <h2>From prototype to App Store</h2>
  <p>I can take an app from an initial workflow through architecture, implementation, testing, App Store packaging, and release. For an existing app, I can also help untangle a feature, improve a rough interface, or prepare the next version without rewriting everything.</p>

  <h2>Typical work</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>SwiftUI and AppKit application development</li>
    <li>Shared iPhone and Mac products</li>
    <li>Local-first and privacy-sensitive tools</li>
    <li>App Store preparation and release</li>
    <li>Maintenance and focused feature work</li>
  </ul>

  <p><a href="/projects/json-assistant">JSON Assistant</a> is a privacy-first native JSON tool for macOS. <a href="/projects/certification-prep-pro">Certification Prep Pro</a> shares a focused study experience across iPhone and Mac.</p>
</ServiceLayout>
